                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d839">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856E.00/8–1847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-20T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 20, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3591. Dutch requested that US ConGen be directed participate in joint report on
                    situation Indonesia with other career Consuls Batavia (<gloss target="#t_urtel1"
                        >urtel</gloss> 4464, Aug 18<note n="3" xml:id="d839fn3">Not printed; it
                        reported a similar request to the British (856E.00/8–1847).</note>). Dept
                    replying that in desire to be helpful is willing for ConGen to join with other
                    career consuls in report but recognizes that arrangements for such report will
                    require careful consideration and must be agreeable both <gloss
                        target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>s and Dutch.</p>
                <p>Sent London as 3591. Repeated Hague as 426, Batavia as 230 and New York as
                    366.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
